ssive entities whose interactions are to be explained by appeal to contingent laws of nature externally imposed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEssentialism (Philosophy). 0aNecessity (Philosophy). 0aPhilosophy of nature. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358171540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773581715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773581715/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles